[[File:Bonk Centre.jpg|thumbnail|Bonk Centre in [[Uusikaupunki]], [[Finland]]]] [[File:Bonk - Paranormal cannon.jpg|thumbnail|"Paranormal cannon" in Bonk Centre]] [[File:Bonk - Raba Hiff machine.jpg|thumbnail|A Raba Hiff machine in Bonk Centre]] '''Bonk Business''' is a [[fictional corporation]] created by Finnish artist and sculptor [[Alvar Gullichsen]]. The "products of Bonk Business" are absurd machines, such as the ''paranormal cannon'', that have no apparent use, and which are built by Gullichsen. The story is that Bonk machines are powered by anchovy oil. The works parody corporate and marketing cliches in a [[retrofuturistic]] style.<ref>[http://www.fastcompany.com/magazine/01/bonk.html The Finnish Company that's Never Done|Fast Company]</ref>
In [[Uusikaupunki]], there is a Bonk museum,<ref>[http://www.bonkcentre.fi/ Bonk Museum]</ref> where Bonk machines are displayed.
