{{italic title}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} [[File:From_Language_to_Language_poster.jpeg|thumb|Film poster]] '''''From Language to Language''''' (Hebrew: '''משפה לשפה''', tr. ''MiSafa LeSafa'') is a 55-minute 2004 Belgian-French-German-Israeli Hebrew-language independent underground experimental documentary art film directed by [[Nurith Aviv]].
==Synopsis== The film, produced by {{ill|Marek Rozenbaum|he|מרק רוזנבאום|pl}} and the [[Dardenne brothers]], was released on DVD by {{ill|Éditions Montparnasse|fr}} as part of a boxset also including 2008’s ''[[Langue sacrée, langue parlée]]'' and 2011’s ''[[Traduire]]'',<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://www.editionsmontparnasse.fr/p1358/Nurith-Aviv-Coffret-DVD|people=Aviv, Nurith|title=''Nurith Aviv (Coffret 3 DVD)''|location=Paris|publisher=Éditions Montparnasse|language=French|accessdate=4 March 2018|format=DVD|oclc=650587091|date=18 May 2011|id=3346030022979|trans-title=''Nurith Aviv (3 DVD Boxset)''}}</ref> with which they form a trilogy.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bar-On|first=Yaakov|date=19 December 2016|script-title=he:נשארת בתמונה|trans-title=She Stays in the Picture|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/MAARIV_2016.pdf|language=Hebrew|work=[[Maariv (newspaper)|Maariv]]|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=28 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''[[The Jerusalem Post]]''|pages=10–11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=8 July 2011|script-title=Rendering a Reborn Tongue|last=Katz|first=Lisa|url=https://www.haaretz.com/1.372135|work=[[Haaretz]]|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=[[M. DuMont Schauberg]] and {{ill|Haaretz Group (Company)|ar|مجموعة هاآرتس|de|Haaretz-Gruppe|he|קבוצת הארץ|lt=Haaretz Group}}|access-date=23 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=1 February 2011|script-title=''Traduire'' – Review|last=Mandelbaum|first=Jacques|author-link=Jacques Mandelbaum|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2011/feb/01/nurith-aviv-film-language-review|work=[[The Guardian]]|location=London|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|access-date=23 April 2018}}</ref> It contains interviews with Israeli artists and writers such as [[Aharon Appelfeld]], [[Evgenia Dodina]], [[Salman Masalha]], [[Agi Mishol]], [[Amal Murkus]], Prof. Dr. {{ill|Haviva Pedaya|he|חביבה פדיה}}, [[Haïm Ulliel]], and [[Meir Wieseltier]] who write in Hebrew even though it is not their native language about the importance of language and asks how the struggle between their mother tongue and Hebrew has affected their art.<ref>{{ill|Yudilovitch, Merav|he|מרב יודילוביץ'}}. {{cite news|date=26 September 2008|script-title=he:ניצחון ההולכים נגד הזרם|trans-title=The Victory of Those Who Go Against the Stream|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-3601999,00.html|language=Hebrew|work=[[Yedioth Ahronoth]]''’s'' ''[[Ynet]]''|location=Rishon LeZion|access-date=4 March 2018|publisher=Yedioth Ahronoth Group}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Anderman, Nirit|he|נירית אנדרמן}}. {{cite news|date=3 February 2012|script-title=he:לדבר קולנועית: ראיון עם הבמאית והצלמת נורית אביב|trans-title=Speaking Film: Interview With Director and Cinematographer Nurith Aviv|url=http://haaretz.co.il/1.1632553|language=Hebrew|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=2 April 2004|script-title=he:רק השפה העברית היא מולדת|trans-title=Only Hebrew Is a Motherland|last=Gur|first=Batya|author-link=Batya Gur|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/misafa/BatiaGour|language=Hebrew|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018|page=113}}</ref><ref>Raizen, Prof. Dr. Esther. [https://www.jstor.org/stable/23062661 ''From Language to Language'']. In: ''Middle East Studies Association Bulletin'', Tucson, Arizona: [[Middle East Studies Association of North America]], Volume 40, Number 1, June 2006, pp. 127–129. Retrieved 24 March 2018.</ref><ref>{{ill|Golan, Dr. Ruth|he|רות גולן}}. שפת האם, שפת האב, השפה הטפילית והשפה הארוטית: על סרטה של נורית אביב '''משפה לשפה''' [Mother Tongue, Father’s Language, Parasitic Language, and Erotic Language: On Nurith Aviv’s Film ''From Language to Language'']. In: {{cite book|date=2007|script-title=he:'''דוקומנטלי: אסופת מאמרים על קולנוע דוקומנטרי ישראלי'''|trans-title=Documentally: Essays on Israeli Documentary Cinema|pages=230–235|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|language=Hebrew|publisher=[[Am Oved]] and New Fund for Cinema and Television|oclc=181631075|url=http://www.am-oved.co.il/page_2452|accessdate=4 April 2018|last=Amir|first=Dr. Maayan, ed.|authorlink=Maayan Amir}} Reprinted in: {{cite book|date=2009|script-title=he:'''נושאי התודעה: כשהפסיכואנליזה פוגשת את התפתחות הרוח'''|trans-title=Consciousness Bearers: When Psychoanalysis Meets Spiritual Development|pages=325–336|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|language=Hebrew|publisher={{ill|Resling|he|רסלינג}}|oclc=757629706|url=http://www.resling.co.il/book.asp?book_id=561|accessdate=4 April 2018|series=Fetish: Original Series of Cultural Critique, Series Editors: {{ill|Dr. Itzhak Benyamini|he|יצחק בנימיני}} and Idan Zivoni|last=Golan|first=Dr. Ruth}}</ref><ref>Caland, Dr. Brigitte. Speaking in Tongues: Film Examines Languages in Israel. In: ''[https://www.google.com/books?id=Qv8PAQAAMAAJ Al Jadid: A Review of Arab Arts and Culture]'', Los Angeles, California: Nagam Cultural Project, Voume 11, Issues 50/51, Winter/Spring 2005, pp. 19–20. Retrieved 4 April 2018.</ref>
==Reception== Between its release and 2006, the film was screened and won several awards at [[Docaviv|DocAviv]], [[Marseille Festival of Documentary Film]], [[Visions du Réel]], [[Internationales Dokumentarfilmfestival München]], [[Musée d'Art et d'Histoire du Judaïsme|Musée d’Art et d’Histoire du Judaïsme]], {{ill|Les 3 Luxembourg|fr}}, {{ill|Espace analytique|fr}}, {{ill|États généraux du film documentaire|fr}}, [[Centre culturel international de Cerisy-la-Salle]], {{ill|Israel Psychoanalytic Society|he|החברה הפסיכואנליטית בישראל}}, [[Strasbourg Museum of Modern and Contemporary Art]], [[Martin-Gropius-Bau]], [[University of Lausanne]], and many other places.<ref>{{cite news|last=Yudilovitch|first=Merav|date=30 March 2004|script-title=he:הזוכה בפסטיבל ״דוקאביב:״ '''משפה לשפה'''|trans-title=The Winner at DocAviv: ''From Language to Language''|url=https://www.ynet.co.il/articles/1,7340,L-2896554,00.html|language=Hebrew|work=Yedioth Ahronoth''’s'' ''Ynet''|location=Rishon LeZion|access-date=26 March 2018|publisher=Yedioth Ahronoth Group}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Schnitzer, Meir|he|מאיר שניצר}}. {{cite news|date=31 March 2004|script-title=he:קלוז־אפ על השונה|trans-title=Closeup on Difference|url=http://www.makorrishon.co.il/nrg/online/archive/ART/680/382.html|language=Hebrew|work=Maariv|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=26 March 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''The Jerusalem Post''}}</ref><ref>{{ill|Pinto, Goel|he|גואל פינטו}}. {{cite news|date=31 March 2004|script-title=DocAviv Prize Goes to Film About Struggling With Hebrew|url=http://haaretz.com/1.4769968|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=4 March 2018}} Hebrew original: {{cite news|last=Pinto|first=Goel|date=30 March 2004|script-title=he:בין שפת התמונות לשפת המלים||trans-title=Between the Language of the Images and the Language of the Words|url=http://haaretz.co.il/1.955929|work=Haaretz|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|publisher=M. DuMont Schauberg and Haaretz Group|access-date=6 October 2018}}</ref> The film was produced by [[ZDF]], [[Arte]], {{ill|Noga Communications|he|נגה תקשורת}}, {{ill|New Fund for Cinema and Television|he|הקרן החדשה לקולנוע וטלוויזיה}}, and {{ill|Israel’s Channel 8|he|ערוץ 8}}. It was also screened at [[Centre Georges Pompidou]] in 2015.<ref>{{cite news|last=Esterkin|first=Jonathan|script-title=he:שפת המוח|trans-title=Language of the Brain|date=15 May 2016|url=http://nurithaviv.free.fr/cerveau/article_presse/maariv1505.jpg|language=Hebrew|work=Maariv|location=Tel Aviv-Yafo|access-date=28 April 2018|publisher=Jerusalem Post Group’s ''The Jerusalem Post''}}</ref>
